      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "bc0ae971378e287ca1046de9f9e788959c5bd36b",
            "subject": "LU-0000 ldlm: limit LDLM_CANCEL_LVB to one Active Writer lock"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-13 22:13:30.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-07-29 17:39:30.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 ldlm: transfer LVB data for Active Writer locks",
        "message": "LU-0000 ldlm: transfer LVB data for Active Writer locks\n\nActive Writer locks with mirror error information need to\ntransfer their LVB data to the server during cancellation\nso the server can update its active writer count and access\nthe mirror error information.\n\nThis patch implements LVB transfer for Active Writer locks\nby:\n\n1. Adding ldlm_should_use_cancel_lvb() to detect Active\n   Writer locks that need LVB transfer\n2. Modifying ldlm_cli_cancel() to use ldlm_cli_cancel_req_lvb()\n   for Active Writer locks instead of regular cancellation\n3. Adding server-side support in mdt_reint_open() to extract\n   and process LVB data from Active Writer lock cancellations\n\nThe LVB transfer ensures that mirror error information\nattached to Active Writer locks is properly communicated\nto the server during lock cancellation, enabling correct\nactive writer count management and error handling.\n\nTest-Parameters: ignore\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9ac8c23725ab196e02d458b079d215d65a34ab73\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master",
      "description": "Edit commit message"
    }
  },
